        <h2>Software features that matter most for plumbers</h2>

        <h3>For service plumbers</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Same-day scheduling and dispatch capability</li>
          <li>Customer history per service address (past repairs, equipment, warranties)</li>
          <li>Mobile quoting and invoicing — collect payment on-site</li>
          <li>Online booking for non-emergency requests</li>
          <li>GPS tracking and route optimization for dispatch</li>
          <li>Automatic review requests after job completion</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>For commercial plumbing subs</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>AIA billing — G702/G703 applications for payment</li>
          <li>Job cost tracking against original bid by cost code</li>
          <li>Change order documentation and GC approval tracking</li>
          <li>Subcontractor compliance (insurance, lien waivers)</li>
          <li>QuickBooks integration for accounting</li>
          <li>Project scheduling with milestone tracking</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Quick picks by business type</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Small service company (1–5 technicians):</strong> Jobber</li>
